I am inspired to use markdown to make HTML5 slides, However the specification is too hard. Actually, I don&rsquo;t know how to make it less ugly, especilly for the first page of the slides.
By chance, I find Torres&rsquo;s slides (Click here), it is made through R using the slidify package. Of course, you also need to write R markdown using Rstudio and Knitr.
Install slidify package in Rstudio install_github('slidify', 'ramnathv') install_github('slidifyLibraries', 'ramnathv')  {:lang=&ldquo;ruby&rdquo;}
